meanings: Chemical Formula C5N5P. A chemical structure of a molecule includes the arrangement of atoms and the chemical bonds that hold the atoms together. The $l^{5}-phosphanepentacarbonitrile molecule contains of 5 Carbon atom(s), 5 Nitrogen atom(s) and 1 Phosphorous atom(s) – a total of 11 atom(s).
